<DOC><DOCNO> AP880324-0072 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-24-88 0948EST</FILEID><FIRST>d a PM-BRF--AutoRecall     03-24 0146</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Auto Recall,0148</SECOND><HEAD>GM Recalls Corvettes, Vans For Safety-Related Problems</HEAD><DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   General Motors Corp. is recalling about 4,9001988 Chevrolet Corvettes to fix defective wheel welds that couldcause the wheel center to separate from the rim during braking orcornering.   The automaker said Wednesday it is also recalling about 460 1987GMC and Chevrolet full-size vans to correct fuel tank filler pipesthat could cause fuel to leak during refueling or turning.   No accidents or injuries have been linked to either problem, GMsaid. Vehicle owners are being notified of the recall by dealers,who will correct the problems at no charge, the company said.   The Corvettes, all equipped with 17-inch wheels, may be missinga weld on some wheels, GM said. The condition could result inpartial loss of steering control and a sudden changed in vehicledirection, the automaker said.</TEXT></DOC>